data.title: Third Way Health raises $15M in Series A funding from Health Velocity Capital, bringing total funding to $22.5M. Expanding AI-powered operations.
data.description: In Los Angeles, Third Way Health, Inc. (TWH), a prominent AI-enabled healthcare services partner, disclosed securing an oversubscribed Series A funding of $15 million from Health Velocity Capital, spearheaded by partner Kristin Torres Mowat. This funding brings the company's total funding to $22.5 million, aiding in further product development and operational expansion. Amidst escalating demands, modern healthcare practices are facing considerable challenges.

data.title: Wasabi Technologies appoints Zachary Smith, digital infra leader, to Board of Directors, with AI driving growth.
data.description: The hot cloud storage company, Wasabi Technologies, based in Boston, recently appointed Zachary Smith to its Board of Directors. Smith, a renowned figure in digital infrastructure and cloud computing, boasts over ten years of expertise in developing and expanding high-performance infrastructure platforms for leading businesses. With the rise of AI shaping Wasabi's future, a notable trend is the increasing number of its top clients originating from the AI sector. This shift indicates a strategic move for Wasabi towards becoming the preferred choice in the cloud storage market.

data.title: Confluent Inc. (Nasdaq: CFLT) enhances real-time data for AI; introduces Confluent Intelligence capabilities for more accurate data analysis.
data.description: In Mountain View, California, Confluent, Inc. (Nasdaq: CFLT) introduced enhanced Confluent Intelligence features facilitating the link between artificial intelligence (AI) agents, leading to more precise and intelligent data analysis. The new Streaming Agents from Confluent leverage the Agent2Agent (A2A) protocol to activate and synchronize external AI agents by utilizing real-time data streams. This advancement simplifies the integration of AI systems throughout businesses. Specifically, the Multivariate Anomaly Detection component is designed to scrutinize data for abnormalities.

data.title: F5 Labs introduces AI Security Index & Agentic Resistance Score to measure AI model risks, with monthly updates.
data.description: Seattle-based company F5 (NASDAQ: FFIV) has unveiled new threat intelligence tools that allow enterprise security leaders to assess and compare the risk levels of various AI models. The Comprehensive AI Security Index (CASI) and Agentic Resistance Score (ARS) leaderboards, developed by the F5 Labs threat research team, offer standardized benchmarks updated monthly. These resources provide real-time data on popular AI models, aiding in the measurement of their security effectiveness.

data.title: Insperity and Workday launch Insperity HRScale for small and mid-sized businesses.
data.description: Insperity, Inc. (NYSE: NSP) and Workday, Inc. (NASDAQ: WDAY) have unveiled the Insperity HRScale™ solution designed for small and midsized businesses. This comprehensive HR services and technology offering merges Insperity’s PEO model with Workday Human, providing a full-service HR support. The solution is now widely accessible following the announcement.

data.title: Heather Kivett joins Industra Talent Partners to enhance capabilities in operations, engineering, and supply chain leadership.
data.description: An accomplished industrial executive recruiter has joined Industra, a San Diego-based company, to enhance its expertise in operations, engineering, and supply chain leadership. This move aims to bolster the company's capabilities in these key areas.

data.title: Icertis releases study on AI in contract management, surveying over 500 practitioners showing increased enthusiasm at 56%.
data.description: In Bellevue, Washington, Icertis, a prominent company in AI-powered contract intelligence, unveiled findings from the fourth annual AI in contract management study by the Commerce & Contract Management (CCM) Institute. The report, titled AI in Contracting 2026: From Experimentation to Impact, is based on input from over 500 professionals in legal, procurement, and finance fields. Results indicate a notable surge in organizational interest in AI, rising from 36% in 2025 to 56% in 2026.

data.title: Panorama Education introduces new AI-powered capabilities for students including assignment tutoring and career exploration.
data.description: Panorama Education, the leading K-12 educational platform, has introduced new AI features for students. This includes an assignment tutor offering real-time academic assistance and a Career and Technical Education (CTE) Pathfinder for graduation tracking and career exploration. These tools are designed with robust privacy controls.

data.title: Moderne launches early-stage program Bauhaus supported by Mango Capital to aid software companies. Includes SpecStory and Serro, starts immediately.
data.description: Miami-based company Moderne unveiled a new program called Bauhaus, supported by Mango Capital, aimed at assisting companies in constructing fundamental systems throughout the software lifecycle. The program kicked off with the participation of initial companies like SpecStory and Serro, marking the beginning of its operations. This initiative signifies a shift in software development towards a more structured approach, indicating a substantial move in the industry.

data.title: C3 AI CEO to speak at two investor conferences on March 2, 2026 - The Citizens Technology Conference and Morgan Stanley Conference.
data.description: C3 AI, a leading Enterprise AI application software company traded on NYSE under the ticker symbol AI, revealed that CEO Stephen Ehikian is set to engage in fireside chats at two upcoming investor conferences. The first conference, The Citizens Technology Conference in San Francisco, CA, will feature the chat on Monday, March 2, 2026, starting at 9:00 am PT. The second event is The Morgan Stanley Technology, Media & Telecom Conference in San Francisco, CA, also on Monday, March 2, 2026.

data.title: ANELLO Photonics and Mythos AI are collaborating to enhance resilient navigation for maritime autonomy by enabling plug-and-play, GPS-denied capabilities for next-gen platforms. News from Feb. 26, 2026.
data.description: A partnership has been formed to develop seamless GPS-denied navigation features for upcoming sea vessels. ANELLO Photonics, known for their Silicon Photonics Optical Gyroscope (SiPhOG™), is leading this initiative. The collaboration, centered on advanced maritime technologies, is set to revolutionize navigation for future vessels. The announcement was made in Santa Clara, California on February 26, 2026. This joint effort aims to enhance navigation capabilities for next-generation maritime platforms by utilizing cutting-edge technology. A major focus of the project is to ensure plug-and-play functionality to navigate without GPS assistance.

data.title: Billion-dollar automotive mega-projects make up 50% of global capital expenditures, with average plant investment increasing by 24%. Site selection now prioritizes execution reliability over incentives.
data.description: Automakers are increasingly finding themselves in direct competition with data centers and semiconductor producers due to growing manufacturing demands. Execution reliability has emerged as the primary factor influencing site selection decisions, surpassing incentives. Elements such as power availability, permitting processes, and workforce accessibility are now critical considerations for automakers aiming to meet the complex manufacturing needs of the industry.

data.title: Chemours plans to offer $600M in senior notes due 2034, subject to market conditions.
data.description: In Wilmington, Delaware, on February 26, 2026, Chemours Company (NYSE: CC) disclosed its plan to propose $600,000,000 in total principal amount for new senior notes set to mature in 2034 (the "Notes"), contingent upon market factors and other conditions. These Notes will hold a senior position...

data.title: Zavation buys ChoiceSpine, making Derek Kuyper CEO, on Feb 26, 2026. It's a portfolio company of Gemspring Capital, designer of spinal implants.
data.description: In Flowood, Mississippi on February 26, 2026, Zavation Medical Products, LLC disclosed their acquisition of Choice Spine Holdings. Zavation, supported by Gemspring Capital, specializes in creating spinal implants, interventional spine products, and biologics. This development marks a significant transaction in the medical industry.

data.title: ArisGlobal launches NavaX Translation to automate global pharmacovigilance translations with TransPerfect, enhancing LifeSphere Safety workflows.
data.description: ArisGlobal, a leading AI-first technology company in the life sciences sector, announced their partnership with TransPerfect Life Sciences on Feb. 26, 2026, in Boston. This strategic collaboration will integrate certified, pharma-grade translation services directly into LifeSphere Safety workflows. The partnership aims to enhance efficiency and accuracy in translations within LifeSphere Safety processes. This development highlights ArisGlobal's commitment to innovation and excellence in the life sciences industry.

data.title: Kettering Foundation grants 5 Global Fellowships for 2026 to leaders in various fields to uphold democracy.
data.description: In Dayton, Ohio on February 26, 2026, the Charles F. Kettering Foundation revealed the selection of five exceptional individuals for one-year global fellowships. These leaders hail from diverse backgrounds such as politics, journalism, and law. The fellowship aims to support them in their efforts to safeguard democracy.
